---
// About section with bio and credentials
---

<section id="about" class="py-16 md:py-24 bg-white">
  <div class="container mx-auto px-4">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto">
      <div class="text-center mb-12">
        <h2
          class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold font-serif text-[var(--color-forest-green)]"
        >
          Meet Kristie
        </h2>
      </div>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8 md:gap-12 items-start">
        <!-- Left: Professional Headshot -->
        <div>
          <img
            src="/headshot.jpeg"
            alt="Kristie Gotwald, Attorney at Law"
            class="rounded-lg shadow-lg w-full"
          />
        </div>

        <!-- Right: Bio Content -->
        <div class="space-y-6">
          <!-- Section: From the Mountains -->
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold font-serif text-[var(--color-forest-green)] mb-4">
              From the Mountains, to the Plains, to the Valley
            </h3>
            <div class="space-y-4">
              <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
                Hailing from the Adirondack Mountains in Upstate New York, Kristie Gotwald moved to
                Ohio in 2007 to study at Cedarville University, where she completed her four-year
                degree in just two and a half years. Following graduation, she and her husband moved
                across the country to follow his military career as she earned her Juris Doctor from the
                University of Oklahoma College of Law in 2012.
              </p>

              <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
                Since she began practicing, she has been named to the National Trial Lawyer's Top 40
                under 40 list for Ohio's criminal defense attorneys, nominated multiple years as Dayton's
                Best Attorney, and served positions of leadership with both the Dayton and Greene
                County Bar Associations.
              </p>

              <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
                She understands the stresses and emotions involved in the cases she faces, helping
                her clients navigate through some of the most difficult times of their lives.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Section: Notable Achievements -->
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold font-serif text-[var(--color-forest-green)] mb-4">
              Notable Achievements
            </h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
              Kristie has been on multiple murder cases and successfully had a client's conviction
              overturned after they'd spent 17 years in prison for a crime they didn't commit.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Bottom Section: Credentials and Family Photo -->
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-8 mt-12 items-stretch">
        <div class="bg-[var(--color-forest-green)] text-white p-6 rounded-lg flex flex-col">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-xl mb-4">
            Licensed in
          </h3>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-lg">
            <li>• Ohio</li>
            <li>• Southern District of Ohio (Federal)</li>
            <li>• New York</li>
            <li>• Oklahoma</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="rounded-lg shadow-lg overflow-hidden">
          <img
            src="/family.jpeg"
            alt="Kristie Gotwald with family"
            class="w-full h-full object-cover"
          />
        </div>

        <div class="bg-[var(--color-gold)] bg-opacity-10 p-6 rounded-lg flex flex-col">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-xl text-[var(--color-forest-green)] mb-4">
            Recognitions
          </h3>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-lg text-gray-700">
            <li>• National Trial Lawyer's Top 40 under 40</li>
            <li>• Dayton's Best Attorney Nominee</li>
            <li>• Bar Association Leadership</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
